Branchiae pectinate with up to 7 filaments, in chaetigers 8–16 (
Figs. 23C
; 
24B
). Number of branchial filaments per chaetiger in order anterior-posterior: 6, 6, 7, 7, 5?, 7, 7, 5, 4. Basal branchial filaments shorter than dorsal cirri.

First two parapodia smallest; most developed in chaetigers 3–24, following ones becoming gradually smaller. Notopodial cirri conical, increasing in size from chaetiger 4 (L5: 
0.48 mm
; Ldc25: 
0.52 mm
), from chaetiger 28, gradually decreasing in size (
Fig. 24A–E
), in specimen 
LACM-AHF
POLY
10193 (Ldc3 
0.31 mm
; Ldc120: 
0.39 mm
) posterior region 1.2 times longer than the pre-branchial region ones. Prechaetal lobes as a transverse fold in all chaetigers (
Fig. 24A–E
). Chaetal lobes in chaetigers 1–18, rounded, shorter than postchaetal lobes, with aciculae emerging dorsal to midline; from chaetiger 19, triangular, longer than other lobes, with acicula emerging in midline (
Fig. 24A–E
). Postchaetal lobes well developed in chaetigers 1–26, bluntly conical, thinner, elongated in branchial region; decreasing in size in chaetigers 14–26, following ones inconspicuous (
Fig. 24A–E
). Ventral cirri digitiform in chaetigers 1–4; in chaetigers 5–25 with oval swollen base and digitiform tip, gradually reducing in size posteriorly; from chaetiger 26, conical (
Fig. 24A–E
).

Aciculae blunt, with reddish basal end, distally translucent (
Fig. 24A–E
). First 15 chaetigers with 2 aciculae; from chaetiger 16, with only one acicula.

Limbate chaetae of two sizes in same chaetiger, larger in anterior region, reduced in number around chaetiger 12. Two 
types
of pectinate chaetae, in anterior chaetigers isodonts narrow with long and slender teeth, with 1–2 pectinate, with up to 8–9 teeth, with transverse distal edge (
Fig. 25C
); in median-posterior chaetigers isodonts narrow with short and slender teeth, 2–3 pectinate, with 10–11 teeth, with transverse distal edge (
Fig. 25D
). Compound falcigers present in all chaetigers; in anterior region with one-sized blade (49 µm, 
Fig. 25A
); all with triangular teeth, of similar size, distal tooth directed upward, proximal tooth directed laterally; in media-posterior chaetigers with all blades of similar size, slightly shorter than blades of anterior chaetigers (43.3 µm, 
Fig. 25B
), with triangular teeth, distal shorter than proximal, distal tooth directed upward, proximal tooth directed laterally. Subacicular hooks bidentate, translucent, starting in chaetiger 28, with one hook per chaetiger; with triangular teeth, distal tooth smaller than proximal, directed upward; proximal tooth directed laterally (
Fig. 25E
).
